<div class="panel panel-primary col-lg-12">
  <div class="panel-heading text-center text-uppercase" style="height:50px; font-size:large"><a style="text-decoration:none; color:White">How to prepare for Outages</a></div>
  <div class="panel-body">
              <ul>
                    <li>Natural Disasters are capable of causing complete destruction to large part of our electric system. </li>
                    <li> It may take time to clear away debris and deliver/repair equipments, and rebuilding.</li>
                    <li>Even with an all-out effort,  some customers may be without power for days.</li>
                </ul>
                <br/>

    <div class="panel panel-primary col-lg-6">
        <div class="panel-heading">
            <h3 class="panel-title text-center">Things To Do:Before Storm</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="panel-body">
               <ul> 
                <li>Set your phone with our Customer Assistance number (XX-XX-XXX).</li>
                <li>If your cell phone is web-enabled, bookmark home page:<i><b style="color:Blue"> www.meralco.com.ph </b></i></li>
                <li>Familiarize yourself with how to report power outages</li>
                <li>Know how to get storm recovery updates and estimated restoration time</li>
                <li>Keep First Aid Kit ready and let your family know about it.</li>
                <li>Keep Emergency Kit ready</li>
                <li>First Aid Kit box</li>
                <li>Flashlight with charged battery</li>
                <li>Whistle to attract attentions for help</li>
                <li>Sufficient stock of water and food</li>
                <li>Bedding and Clothes bag for each person packed</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="panel panel-primary col-lg-6">
        <div class="panel-heading ">
            <h3 class="panel-title text-center">Things to Do : During  and After Storm </h3>
        </div>
        <div class="panel-body">
             <ul>
               <li>Field reports are received and assessed for severity of damage. </li>
               <li>Stay Up to Date on the changing weather conditions.</li>
               <li>Ensure your batteries are fully charged  all the time.</li>
               <li> Set your Refrigerator and Freezer controls to coldest setting.</li>
               <li> If cleaning debris, Do not pile up them near poles or equipments.</li>
               <li> If Power line fallen on car, stay inside home and wait for crew to arrive.</li>
               <li>Keep your Car fuel filled full tank.</li>
               <li>Do not depend upon ATM for later, Keep sufficient cash.</li>
               <li>Follow the safety instruction while using backup generator.</li>
               <li>Keep Children away from the debris.</li>
               <li>Disconnect all appliances from sockets  once power is out.</li>
             </ul>
        </div>
    </div>


  </div>
</div>


